      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(mattermost): backfill thread history from server when in-memory window is empty",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Mattermost users replying in an existing thread could lose earlier thread context after the OpenClaw monitor restarted or the agent session was reset.\n\nFixes #93204\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe Mattermost monitor now backfills a cold local thread-history window from the Mattermost thread endpoint before building the inbound context. The backfill is scoped to the Mattermost thread and current agent session, so normal same-session follow-ups do not keep refetching after the turn kernel clears pending history, while a reset session can recover the thread again.\n\n## User Impact\n\nMattermost thread replies keep useful prior context after restart or `/new`, without adding repeated server-thread fetches to ordinary same-session follow-ups.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.inbound-system-event.test.ts`: 11 passed; covers the monitor path, cold thread backfill, same-session no-refetch, and session-key rotation.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.test.ts`: 61 passed; covers backfill windowing, current-post filtering, populated-window marking, and reset-session refetch.\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions:test`: passed.\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.test.ts extensions/mattermost/src/mattermost/monitor.inbound-system-event.test.ts`: passed.\n- `git diff --check`: passed.\n\nLive proof: local Docker Mattermost Team Edition 10.11.21 at `http://localhost:8065`, with tokens and Mattermost ids redacted. The proof used real Mattermost REST auth, posts, and `/api/v4/posts/<root>/thread` history through `monitorMattermostProvider`; a fake websocket only injected `posted` events into the monitor. Observed dispatch context included the prior root/thread messages on cold start and again after simulating a new agent session for the same Mattermost thread:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mattermost\": \"10.11.21 local Docker, token/id redacted\",\n  \"dispatchCount\": 2,\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"firstColdStartContainsPriorThreadContext\": true,\n  \"firstColdStartContainsRootContext\": true,\n  \"restartSameThreadContainsPriorThreadContext\": true\n}\n```\n\nAI-assisted: built with Codex\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93204-Mattermost--thread-context-los",
